parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering hose can cause fluid to leak onto the hot exhaust manifold, leading to a fire hazard, loss of power steering, and potentially causing accidents or property damage.
symptoms: Power steering fluid leaking onto the exhaust manifold
smoke or fire from under the hood
loss of power steering
difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to complete the recall on the power steering hose can lead to continued safety hazards, including fire and loss of control.
symptoms: Power steering hose failure despite recall completion
lack of notification of recall
inadequate repair or replacement of power steering hose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the occupant to be improperly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is broken
the release button is broken
the buckle is hard to lock
the buckle locks up hard to unlock
the seat belt will not latch
the seat belt does not retract as intended
the seat belt does not rewind when unbuckled
resulting in excessive slack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to retract properly can cause the occupant to be improperly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract as intended
the seat belt does not rewind when unbuckled
resulting in excessive slack
the seat belt will not retract back when released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inoperability of the seat belt can cause the occupant to be improperly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is broken
the seat belt will not latch
the seat belt is hard to lock
the seat belt locks up hard to unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Pipe Rust and Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and leakage of the fuel filler pipe can cause fuel to leak onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the filler pipe
fuel spills on the ground while filling up
fuel smell or odor near the filler pipe
rust or corrosion visible on the filler pipe.
